+------------------------------------------+
|       PSI/O SYSTEM (Basic Boot ROM)      |
|  (Initialisation and I/O Handler Logic)  |
+------------------------------------------+
|                                          |
|  1. POWER-ON RESET CIRCUITRY (POR)       |
|  (Forces PC to address 0000 upon startup)|
+------------------------------------------+
|                                          |
|  2. INITIALISATION ROM (4x4 bit)         |
|  (Read-Only Memory mapped to low addresses)
|  +-------------------------------------+ |
|  | Location 0000: Initialisation Code  | |
|  | Location 0001: Load Routine Address | |
|  | Location 0002: Check I/O Status     | |
|  | Location 0003: JUMP to User Program | |
|  +-------------------------------------+ |
+------------------------------------------+
|                                          |
|  3. I/O HANDLER LOGIC                    |
|  (Simple logic to read/write I/O ports)  |
|  +-------------------------------------+ |
|  | DECODER: Selects Input Switch (Read)| |
|  | LATCH: Stores Output LED State      | |
|  +-------------------------------------+ |
+------------------------------------------+
|                                          |
|  BUS INTERFACE: Connects to Address Bus  |
|  and 1-bit Data Bus (for instruction fetch)
+------------------------------------------+

